    "body": "Code like this shouldn't even compile:\n```\ncdef int raiseit(self):\n    raise IndexError\n```\nIt's certainly not possible to fix this in the general case, e.g.\n```\ncdef int raiseit(self):\n    try:\n        raise IndexError\n    except SomeException:\n        pass\n```\nbut at least if there isn't any try-except block around a ```raise``` statement, this should result in a compile time error. In other cases without an explicit raise statement but where an exception may occur, a visible compile time warning would be nice.\n\nMigrated from http://trac.cython.org/ticket/370",
